<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-05T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-05T21:00:00-05:00" n="683" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d683">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.51/1735: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-05T21:00:00-05:00">March 5, 1940—9
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>54. Discussions still continue with Council but hope for favorable result
                            tomorrow. Please try to hold matters open. Possibly Aranha <pb facs="0604" n="592" xml:id="pg_592"/> could obtain authority to make
                            offer immediately upon receiving proposed assurances.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>